gomodel:SYNGO_249  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: It is shown that postsynaptic perfusion with PKM zeta (a constitutively active splice variant of the PRKCZ gene) increases postsynaptic AMPAR responses. This is inhibited by pep2m, a peptide that inhibits NSF/GluR2 interactions (Figure 1). The effect does not require exocytotic insertion of GluRs, since Botox B is unable to inhibit the effect (Figure 1D), and there is no increase in the surface or total level or GluR2 (Figure 3E). Using synaptosomes, it is shown that PKM-zeta dependent LTP does lead to a increase in synaptic GluR2 and GluR3, and that this is blocked by pep2m and a ZIP (a inhibitor with some specificity to PKM-zeta). It is thus concluded that PKM-zeta increases AMPAR responses by recruiting extrasynaptic GluRs to the PSD.\n\nLing et.al. 2006 demonstrates that PKM zeta-induced potentiation requires an increase in the number of receptors, not an increase in receptor conductance.\n\nIt should be noted that PKM-zeta has long been suspected to be essential for postsynaptic LTP, but that this is subject on an ongoing debate. (Tsokas et.al. 2016).. Experimental description: For experiments in Figures 1-4 and supplemental Figures 1-6\n(available at www.jneurosci.org as supplemental material), hippocampi\nof male, 3- to 4-week-old Sprague Dawley rats were removed after\ndecapitation under halothane-induced anesthesia, according to State\nUniversity of New York Downstate Medical Center Animal Use and Care\nCommittee standards.\n\n13/3/2017 Pim\n-Species of the PKMzeta infused recombinant protein is not explicitly stated. The authors were contacted. The authors responded:\n\nFrom: Todd Sacktor [Todd.Sacktor@downstate.edu]\nSent: 13 March 2017 15:11\nTo: Nierop, P. van\nSubject: Re: PKMzeta species information [pmid:18667614]\n\nDear Pim, it is rat. Thanks, Todd\n\n- Annotation made against rat." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_249" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

